narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Language, culture, societal issues in Indonesia.
I learned a lot of new vocabulary and culture about Indonesia!
We delved deeper into Indonesian culture, politics, and language in the context of current events. Added more vocabulary.
I learned so much about the Indonesian culture and the different aspects of society and how it compares to America.
I learned so much about the Indonesian culture and religion! Fascinating class!

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Each class have a new angle of Indonesian studies.
Great class structure, great discussions, and great content.
This course is great! I really like how she catered the course to our specific interests.
No weaknesses in this course! Super interesting and obviously Bu is the absolute greatest!

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes. Take Indonesian!! You will thank yourself.
Yes, going deep into the language was a great choice and I've enjoyed the opportunity to move beyond language into culture.
Yes! My favorite class I have taken at Yale. Bu Dinny is the most engaging professor and really gets to know all her students well!
Absolutely 100%! If you really want to get the most out of your indo experience it is a must take!
